FBIS4-67704 "jptep009___94063" JPRS-TEP-94-009 JPRS Epidemiology 27 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA IRAN Ministry Reports Construction of Rural Medical Centers Ministry Reports Construction of Rural Medical Centers NC2703202894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0345 GMT 27 Mar 94 NC2703202894 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Commentary by News Research and Commentary Group] [Excerpt] [Passage omittted] The Health, Treatment, and Medical Education Ministry spent 2 billion rials and, in addition, the World Bank collaborated and allocated $300 million for the construction of rural medical and treatment centers. The rate of increase of Iran's population in the past year was reduced from 3.2 percent to 2.2 percent. With its population control, the Islamic Republic of Iran has reduced the average number of children in a family from five to 3.2. On this basis, the family planning program was pursued intensively and seriously. [passage omitted]
